      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BENNIE AND THE JETS NZ (2) kept his manners in check and was back in the winners' list here last week, giving him four wins and a G3 placing from his last six starts. Overcame a back row draw last time so looks well served by this draw and owns a good record at this longer distance. GEE CEE CALDER (4) has come from back row draws to finish fourth in her two starts at this venue since a spell. Should be close to peak fitness now and gets her chance from a more favourable barrier. Hard to knock the recent consistency of THE SKY IS THE LIMIT (5) who added to a string for top-four finishes when beaten less than 2m here last week and came from a similar draw to this when winning at Geelong two back. OX KNOX (9) is good enough to make an impact in this line-up if things go his way from the second line.",
